FabMo Loom is part of the FabMo platform, from the makers of ShopBot
(https://www.shopbottools.com). It was developed at ShopBot Labs
(https://labs.shopbottools.com).

This product includes clipper-lib (Clipper, by Angus Johnson; JavaScript
port by Timo), used under the Boost Software License 1.0, vendored at
vendor/clipper.js.

The built-in signage glyph library (app/glyphs.mjs) is derived from the
AIGA/U.S. Department of Transportation symbol signs (1974/1979), which
AIGA makes available copyright-free, plus the International Symbol of
Access. Source files were obtained via Wikimedia Commons and processed
into region-native SVG for CNC use.
